ŁThe Family of Professor Horace David Ritchie
Dedicate this bench to The Royal Parks
which they treasure.
Gordon, Andrew, Bruce, Blaise,
Maximillian, Ben, Imogen and Maya"Č
│Nowhere is more loved than this treasured
place where joyous times are shared with
family, friends and all who stop to wonder al
the beauty surrounding them. Christine Kitchen."Č
│[{"URL":"/image/14d226c4b31ed91ce0fc9bb7efb20692e8f39a22","importURL":"http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Memorial_bench_for_James_A._G._Goldfinger_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1510900.jpg","licence":"CC BY-SA 2.0","media_type":"bench","sha1":"14d226c4b31ed91ce0fc9bb7efb20692e8f39a22","width":640,"height":480}]"╝
╣Joseph Rifkind & Renee Rifkind
Walked and sat here every day, it was their special place.
They are remembered by their children:
Marion, Gabrielle and Charles
and their 10 grandchildren"Į
║In memory of
Derek Lane
From a select number of friends who spent many happy
hours in his company and together enjoyed the splendour
of this city and the tranquility of these gardens"Š
